{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make CMS payments stop if Court Order is ignored regarding access",
        "additional_details": "If this rule were put in place things would quickly change and a fairer system would happen overnight. The absent parent, who is spending thousands in legal fees just to be involved, remains unheard/unimportant unless it\u2019s regarding CMS payments!!! Zero contact with their children even after being granted it through the Courts is unacceptable yet CMS payments are still to be paid!!\r\n",
        "background": "Parents who ignore Court Orders regarding visitation with the absent parent should not receive maintenance payments. It\u2019s a fact that the CMS states: you do not pay maintenance in order to see your child, however, too many full time parents are ignoring Court Orders with no consequence.",
